{
  "texts": [
    "Zero-Shot Prompting refers to a scenario where an LLM is prompted for a task or a query without any prior examples.",
    "The model must rely solely on pretrained knowledge and understanding to generate a response or solution.",
    "Few-shot prompting involves providing the LLM with a few examples before prompting it to perform a task.",
    "These examples serve as a guide, helping the model understand the expected response or output.",
    "It is particularly useful when the LLM must be adapted to a specific type of task or format that it might not have been explicitly trained on, e.g., TS generation."
  ]
}